This is kind of a progress log for the development of AliceOS.
Future phases and plans will be very vague and subject to change.
Please do not expect any of them to come true.
Tasks aren't exactly ordered.

Legend:
- To do
X Done
P Partial
F Failed

Shanghai phase:
  X Start project
  F Follow JamesM's tutorial step by step
  X Restart project
  X VGA text mode
  X Implement printk()
  X Serial port driver
  X Memory and string functions
  X Extended VGA graphics
  X Commandline handling
  X Ramdisk support
  X Framebuffer console
  X BGA driver (Bochs/QEMU)
  X GDT, IDT...
  X IRQs
  X PIT
  - Fix generic VGA drivers to work on real hardware (very hard)
  - Keyboard input
  P Dynamic memory (kalloc/krealloc/kfree)
  X Paging
  - Basic PCI/PCI-e support (required for more drivers)
  - VMWare graphics driver
  - BGA linear framebuffer
  - ACPI interface
  - Multitasking
  - Executable loader (last step, very very important to reach Hourai phase)
Hourai phase:
  - Loadable kernel modules
  - Move drivers to individual modules
France:
  - Generic PATA/SATA drivers
  - Generic USB drivers
  - PC speaker driver
  - USB keyboard and USB mouse drivers
  - Virtual Filesystem
  - Filesystem modules
     - AOSRD
     - AOSRD2
     - tmpfs
     - FAT32
     - ext2
     - ReiserFS
  - Basic NVIDIA video driver
  - Basic Intel video driver
  - Basic ATI video driver
Holland:
  - Audio subsystem
  - Specific audio drivers
     - SB16
     - AC97 / HD Audio
     - ES1370
  - Attempt to get help from GPU manufacturers for more specialized drivers
     - NVIDIA
     - Intel
     - ATI
  - OpenGL implementation
Tibet:
  - AOS C Library
  - Alice in Userland
  - Cross-compilers
     - GCC
     - Clang
  - Miscellaneous system scripts
  - /sbin/init, init scripts
  - Graphics server/compositor
  - Window manager
  - Graphical applications
Kyoto:
  - Low-level networking system
  - Ethernet...
  - Wireless...
  - Bluetooth...
London:
  - Other misc hardware drivers
